01:25:46,395 --> 01:25:52,303
Hi all, I'm Angela Moore and I'm on Vine Street in Medford.

503
01:25:54,063 --> 01:26:00,545
So we wanted to come before you folks and before the community to ask some questions that we had and concerns that we had.

504
01:26:01,106 --> 01:26:06,407
I know that you know Angela and I as regular attendees of the school committee meetings.

505
01:26:06,427 --> 01:26:07,848
We've been coming for several years.

506
01:26:08,848 --> 01:26:10,969
Also have children in the school district.

507
01:26:11,029 --> 01:26:14,170
I have two high schoolers and a elementary schooler.

508
01:26:14,190 --> 01:26:22,153
I'm also the co-chair of the Medford Special Education Parent Advisory Council, representing approximately 800 families in the district.

509
01:26:23,484 --> 01:26:36,127
And one of the things we wanted to talk about was it was really, really interesting to watch tonight's events because so much of what I feel like we all watch tonight is family and community engagement.

510
01:26:37,087 --> 01:26:41,688
And it's an important part of what we really need to have as Medford moves forward.

511
01:26:41,788 --> 01:26:50,430
I hope that Dr. Edward Vincent watches these archival meetings to understand what it is we are looking for and what we need.

512
01:26:50,550 --> 01:26:59,892
And everyone knows that we had a very unfortunate event and we had an unfortunate meeting that occurred in February where there was a lot of heated emotions and where there was a lot of

513
01:27:02,444 --> 01:27:05,866
And people talked about that for a long time in the community afterwards.

514
01:27:05,906 --> 01:27:10,330
And they talked about how terrible that meeting was in so many different ways.

515
01:27:10,550 --> 01:27:16,155
And what wasn't talked about, unfortunately, in my opinion, was what brought that about.

516
01:27:16,675 --> 01:27:24,001
Not so much the incident itself, but the lack of family and community engagement in our community.

517
01:27:24,882 --> 01:27:31,307
Even this context where you have to be willing to stand up at a podium and speak into a microphone.

518
01:27:32,627 --> 01:27:38,248
with your back turned to the rest of the community to be able to converse and express what your feelings are.

519
01:27:38,729 --> 01:27:42,929
I mean, I went on to the website earlier today to just sort of look at what the protocol is.

520
01:27:43,009 --> 01:27:46,030
And I understand protocol and the need for protocol.

521
01:27:46,150 --> 01:27:49,771
You have to get the business part of it going and the meeting moving along.

522
01:27:50,751 --> 01:27:54,352
You know, but the website is you have to submit in writing your request.

523
01:27:54,372 --> 01:27:55,692
You have to do it a week ahead of time.

524
01:27:55,712 --> 01:27:57,053
You have exactly three minutes.

525
01:27:57,093 --> 01:27:59,053
You can come up to the podium and you can talk to us.

526
01:28:00,323 --> 01:28:02,584
That's not family and community engagement.

527
01:28:03,464 --> 01:28:07,226
I had the benefit last year of going to graduate school, and I really enjoyed my time there.

528
01:28:07,246 --> 01:28:16,450
I had a great teacher who helped write for the Department of Education at the federal level the family and community engagement guidelines and some material there.

529
01:28:16,550 --> 01:28:20,112
And one of the things they talk about is family and community.

530
01:28:20,152 --> 01:28:21,492
We're all part of the community.

531
01:28:21,512 --> 01:28:23,373
So the teachers that came up tonight are the community.

532
01:28:23,413 --> 01:28:25,554
The school committee members are the community.

533
01:28:26,034 --> 01:28:27,275
Our shop owners are the community.

534
01:28:27,315 --> 01:28:28,375
The parents are the community.

535
01:28:28,715 --> 01:28:29,996
We're not just families.

536
01:28:30,496 --> 01:28:35,205
or teachers or people that don't have children.

537
01:28:35,485 --> 01:28:36,908
We're all a community together.

538
01:28:36,928 --> 01:28:40,274
I had this really great experience last week where

539
01:28:41,386 --> 01:28:48,332
I set up an appointment to talk with our new EL director, Paul Texera, and we had the best conversation.

540
01:28:48,652 --> 01:28:59,440
We sat in his office for just about an hour, and I learned a little bit about him, he learned a little bit about me, and we both walked away from that experience wanting to work together and really wanting to collaborate with each other.

541
01:29:00,001 --> 01:29:05,385
And I thought, you know, what would have happened if we hadn't built those relationships with each other, if we didn't know each other?

542
01:29:05,885 --> 01:29:07,587
And that's what family and community engagement is.

543
01:29:07,647 --> 01:29:10,389
It's about building relationships and about knowing each other.

544
01:29:11,070 --> 01:29:21,960
Folks might recall when this all happened a few months ago, there was a post on social media where one of Mr. Belson's family members talked about who Mr. Belson is as a man.

545
01:29:23,155 --> 01:29:26,537
And we heard from his friend earlier talking about who Mr. Belson is as a man.

546
01:29:27,138 --> 01:29:32,642
And personalizing Mr. Belson and personalizing each one of us is what builds community and relationship.

547
01:29:32,962 --> 01:29:38,726
And I think people are able to relate much better to who he was as a man because we learned about who you are as a man.

548
01:29:39,246 --> 01:29:42,228
Tonight, seeing you apologize, we learned about who you are as a man.

549
01:29:42,789 --> 01:29:45,230
And that's the important piece of family and community engagement.

550
01:29:45,330 --> 01:29:47,071
It's collaboration and communication.

551
01:29:47,432 --> 01:29:48,572
We're not doing it enough.

552
01:29:48,973 --> 01:29:50,274
And we can't say enough about that.

553
01:29:50,314 --> 01:29:51,715
And that's why I stand before you tonight

554
01:29:52,666 --> 01:29:55,828
for more family and community collaboration.

555
01:29:56,248 --> 01:29:57,289
Bring people to the table.

556
01:29:57,329 --> 01:29:58,390
I was watching Justin tonight.

557
01:29:58,410 --> 01:29:59,891
I'm so glad Justin's here.

558
01:30:00,671 --> 01:30:01,972
That's a relatively new thing.

559
01:30:02,132 --> 01:30:03,193
That's a great thing.

560
01:30:04,373 --> 01:30:08,876
More roundtable discussion, not having to come up to the podium and ask and talk.

561
01:30:08,956 --> 01:30:10,677
Or you guys were inundated with emails.

562
01:30:10,717 --> 01:30:12,298
I'm glad you were inundated with emails.

563
01:30:12,358 --> 01:30:14,460
I say to anybody watching tonight, keep them coming.

