01:30:14,840 --> 01:30:20,523
Keep communicating, please, because we need you to communicate to make a difference and to make things transparent.

565
01:30:21,624 --> 01:30:31,970
So getting to the transparent piece, even in the past few months with everything that's been going on, there's still been sort of concerns around some of the transparency.

566
01:30:32,170 --> 01:30:38,173
And what you saw the night in February and what I witnessed, which was, frankly, traumatizing for me.

567
01:30:38,213 --> 01:30:44,497
I don't know about other people, but I was sort of shell-shocked when I left there at the anger and the vitriol that was there that night.

568
01:30:44,917 --> 01:30:47,939
But I was also really very clear what the message was.

569
01:30:48,099 --> 01:30:50,120
And it was, we don't feel like we're being heard.

570
01:30:50,561 --> 01:30:59,984
And in any relationship, as people can attest in their marriage or their relationship with their children or what have you, when you feel like you're not being heard, what typically happens?

571
01:31:00,604 --> 01:31:01,144
You yell.

572
01:31:01,344 --> 01:31:02,025
You're angry.

573
01:31:02,825 --> 01:31:04,125
You get out of control.

574
01:31:05,326 --> 01:31:07,166
But when you're being heard, you're collaborating.

575
01:31:07,186 --> 01:31:08,006
You're working together.

576
01:31:08,166 --> 01:31:09,167
So that's what we need to do.

577
01:31:09,687 --> 01:31:19,670
So in the most recent Committee of the Whole meeting, when we found out by social media that the decision to extend the superintendent's contract went from

578
01:31:20,425 --> 01:31:24,988
April to June, that was not family and community engagement.

579
01:31:25,428 --> 01:31:29,150
