616
01:34:54,718 --> 01:35:07,280
Like, I feel like some things deserve to at least have a conversation about whether they should be redacted from the release, or to ask, you know, our lawyer, should this be included in the release?

617
01:35:08,400 --> 01:35:10,040
And I just have not been able to get through.

618
01:35:10,080 --> 01:35:19,362
Now, I do believe I released to the committee, I don't remember if I released it to the public, the purely, you know,

619
01:35:20,055 --> 01:35:26,658
the statistics kind of stuff, which doesn't have anything interesting, like what percentage were men and women and all that other stuff.

620
01:35:28,720 --> 01:35:32,642
So if that hasn't been released, I can certainly release that.

621
01:35:33,322 --> 01:35:39,345
But honestly, the important and interesting stuff is not in the numbers.

622
01:35:41,938 --> 01:35:46,459
There's just really very little surprising in the numbers, although you should still be able to see them.

623
01:35:47,399 --> 01:35:51,261
It's in that really detailed stuff that people had to say.

624
01:35:51,281 --> 01:35:57,362
And believe me, people had a lot to say on the 470 responses or so.

625
01:35:58,362 --> 01:36:01,003
There was nobody who didn't have a lot to say.

626
01:36:01,123 --> 01:36:04,424
So that's what I had to say about the survey.

627
01:36:05,044 --> 01:36:11,146
If I could just add on the survey, it was used for the search committee purposes to get the search committee off the ground.

628
01:36:12,390 --> 01:36:17,033
Everything that happened in the search committee was executive session, basically, the equivalent of it.

629
01:36:17,453 --> 01:36:23,557
So now that we're out, you should turn them over and we can redact if there's something offensive.

630
01:36:24,338 --> 01:36:26,179
But otherwise, it's benign.

631
01:36:26,979 --> 01:36:27,139
Ms.

632
01:36:27,159 --> 01:36:27,680
Van de Kloot?

633
01:36:28,160 --> 01:36:31,722
Melanie, I just wanted to mention one thing.

634
01:36:31,742 --> 01:36:40,408
I think that your call for community and family engagement was heard very much by the school committee and is reflected in the choice of our new superintendent.

635
01:36:41,497 --> 01:36:49,182
Certainly, as we went about interviewing people and talking to them, that was a major concern.

636
01:36:49,562 --> 01:37:00,628
And in fact, we've picked someone who we feel will be able to broaden family engagement and reach into communities that perhaps have been, not perhaps, but have been underrepresented.

637
01:37:01,449 --> 01:37:09,133
So I think that that is an extremely important point and that we heard you very clearly

638
01:37:10,017 --> 01:37:19,082
and know that that is a concern that we would like to make sure that we're broadening community and family engagement.

639
01:37:20,062 --> 01:37:28,226
By the way, one of the things that you mentioned about the podium and the way you come here, that's one of the reasons why many of us actually prefer committees of the whole, because it's a much more

640
01:37:28,811 --> 01:37:35,776
feeling of collaborative discussion when we're around the table versus here, which is a much more formal presentation.

641
01:37:36,257 --> 01:37:41,541
And remember, as you speak, part of the thing is your face is to the camera.

642
01:37:42,141 --> 01:37:49,227
And so while you're here, it's always awkward because your face is, you know, your back is to the community, but there's the larger community at home.

643
01:37:52,229 --> 01:37:56,052
And as far as that meeting, it was a special meeting of the school committee.

644
01:37:56,072 --> 01:37:57,073
It was not a committee of the whole,

645
01:37:57,973 --> 01:37:59,094
It's a nomenclature, right?

646
01:37:59,134 --> 01:37:59,554
Same thing.

647
01:38:00,054 --> 01:38:02,955
But that was posted the way all of the meetings were posted.

648
01:38:02,975 --> 01:38:06,077
And I know there were some parents that did show up at that meeting.

649
01:38:06,177 --> 01:38:13,040
And we held it before the Honor Society meeting, because three of us went over to that right from the end of that meeting.

650
01:38:13,780 --> 01:38:15,841
So it was public.

651
01:38:16,161 --> 01:38:19,342
It was as public as any other meeting that we hold, just like tonight.

652
01:38:23,284 --> 01:38:23,944
Mr. Ruggiero.

653
01:38:24,344 --> 01:38:25,765
How the issue was brought up

654
01:38:27,282 --> 01:38:32,668
It was, I was under the impression that we were going to discuss the transition strategy.

655
01:38:33,789 --> 01:38:35,531
That is the notice that was made.

656
01:38:36,532 --> 01:38:45,942
I didn't, it would have probably been more helpful to the community and to me as a member if the discussion was about continuing Roy Belson's contract.

657
01:38:47,700 --> 01:38:56,064
Because I wasn't, personally, I wasn't really prepared to have all the reasons and to rehash through the argument other than what I did.

658
01:38:57,584 --> 01:38:58,505
But I share your concerns.

659
01:38:59,631 --> 01:39:07,294
because I do believe that it was an important decision to make, and I think more community input would have been very helpful, as I made clear during the meeting.

660
01:39:07,314 --> 01:39:20,298
Actually, if I could, the meeting posting said the purpose of the meeting is to determine administrative leadership of the school system from May 1st to June 30th, 2018, and to take appropriate actions to implement the same.

661
01:39:20,738 --> 01:39:25,240
Further, the school committee may discuss relevant transition plans consistent with the completion

662
01:39:25,758 --> 01:39:27,919
of the superintendent search and selection process.

663
01:39:28,119 --> 01:39:36,223
Yeah, but it doesn't say that Roy, just a clarification, it does not say that in addition, Roy Bellson's contract may be extended.

664
01:39:36,523 --> 01:39:42,626
The idea of the, while what we, I do not claim that what we did was a violation of open meeting law, I don't think so.

665
01:39:42,726 --> 01:39:43,066
It wasn't.

666
01:39:43,106 --> 01:39:49,829
But it would have been more clear to the community if that issue of Roy Bellson's extended contract was made more clear.

667
01:39:50,909 --> 01:39:51,369
And thank you.

668
01:39:51,429 --> 01:39:55,091
And Madam Mayor, respectfully, I agree.

669
01:39:55,211 --> 01:40:06,675
I think that I didn't go to the meeting myself because I thought that it was a sort of procedural interim, you know, what we were going to do, which I thought was pretty clear that it would likely be deputies.

670
01:40:08,336 --> 01:40:12,998
Obviously, I was uninformed, but it didn't say specifically about Mr. Belson.

671
01:40:13,178 --> 01:40:15,319
Had it, I would have been at the meeting.

672
01:40:16,718 --> 01:40:17,299
Excuse me.

673
01:40:17,319 --> 01:40:18,440
So I think that that's the point.

674
01:40:18,480 --> 01:40:19,541
I'm sorry.

675
01:40:19,701 --> 01:40:22,163
The committee could vote anything that night.

676
01:40:22,183 --> 01:40:24,045
It wasn't dictated what was going to happen.

677
01:40:24,065 --> 01:40:24,245
Right.

678
01:40:24,405 --> 01:40:24,946
I understand.

679
01:40:24,966 --> 01:40:25,906
I totally understand that.

680
01:40:25,926 --> 01:40:33,353
But I guess what I'm saying in the interest of family and community engagement, we didn't hear that and we didn't hear what we needed to hear to be at the meeting.

681
01:40:33,413 --> 01:40:36,476
And so from a family perspective, it wasn't communicated effectively.

682
01:40:37,772 --> 01:40:46,057
And to add on to that point, I mean, I would like to suggest that these important decisions are made during regular committee meetings.

683
01:40:46,777 --> 01:40:57,702
I understand that sometimes we do need to go into executive session or committee of the wholes, but that particular issue should have been televised so the whole community could hear it.

684
01:40:58,643 --> 01:41:04,286
It's unfortunate that the community had to sort of hear about it secondhand.

685
01:41:04,346 --> 01:41:06,387
It creates an environment of mistrust.

686
01:41:07,862 --> 01:41:08,182
Thank you.

687
01:41:08,482 --> 01:41:09,423
Mr. Russo's next.

688
01:41:12,644 --> 01:41:22,248
My question, you mentioned about this format, which I don't think anybody actually thinks this is the most enjoyable format, especially that one spot.

689
01:41:22,368 --> 01:41:25,169
This is actually much less of a challenge than that spot.

690
01:41:25,529 --> 01:41:36,234
But I'm just curious, and I'm not a history teacher, and I have no civics education other than the one I got in high school, but are there other formats for this

691
01:41:37,048 --> 01:41:41,670
are implemented in this country that people know of?

692
01:41:41,970 --> 01:41:46,212
Or is this really, I mean, I just sort of assume this is the default format everywhere.

693
01:41:47,773 --> 01:41:55,116
I think that you look, there can be something as simple as handheld microphones and people could stand at either end and address all of you.

694
01:41:56,157 --> 01:42:01,279
It's simple if you think outside of the box a little bit about, well, what feels welcoming and this is not welcoming.

695
01:42:02,220 --> 01:42:02,980
It's intimidating.

696
01:42:03,421 --> 01:42:05,723
And so what do we do to make somebody feel less intimidated?

697
01:42:05,783 --> 01:42:06,684
And I couldn't agree more.

698
01:42:06,704 --> 01:42:09,086
I think Dr. Edward Vincent is going to be all over that.

699
01:42:09,686 --> 01:42:11,748
And I'm really happy and very pleased.

700
01:42:11,768 --> 01:42:13,649
And thank you all very much for your hard work on that.

701
01:42:13,689 --> 01:42:15,011
I know how hard you worked on that.

702
01:42:15,051 --> 01:42:17,933
And thank you for the privilege of being on the superintendent search committee.

703
01:42:18,093 --> 01:42:18,914
It was a great privilege.

704
01:42:20,075 --> 01:42:20,275
Yeah.

705
01:42:20,955 --> 01:42:21,276
Thank you.

706
01:42:22,757 --> 01:42:23,477
Mr. Benedetto.

707
01:42:23,658 --> 01:42:23,978
Thank you.

708
01:42:24,158 --> 01:42:25,519
I actually requested the meeting.

709
01:42:26,380 --> 01:42:28,942
I requested the meeting because May 1st was coming.

710
01:42:29,894 --> 01:42:42,578
and my understanding that Mr. Belson was retiring as of April 30th, and that we needed to have an official person named as acting superintendent to get us through the transition.

711
01:42:43,198 --> 01:42:57,422
So I had no idea that there were other options at play that were gonna be presented that evening, so I too was shocked that this came up at this meeting,

712
01:42:59,435 --> 01:43:13,422
I assumed the vote of the committee, and when the committee voted to extend him to April 30th, I took on that as that's my new role, is to support him till that point, and then make sure our district has somebody at the helm.

713
01:43:14,102 --> 01:43:16,343
So I really pushed to have this meeting.

714
01:43:18,324 --> 01:43:25,648
So it was a little quicker than some, and it was a special meeting to discuss it, my understanding that is

715
01:43:26,212 --> 01:43:38,877
someone within the district would step into that role, whether a deputy, a principal, someone we felt confident, you know, to help us through because Mr. Belson was also going to be present.

716
01:43:39,337 --> 01:43:48,140
And knowing him, as we all do, we know he works way beyond the hours required, and he was being contracted to continue for 25 hours.

717
01:43:48,440 --> 01:43:52,962
So he was accessible to help with any bigger issues, and I'm sure

718
01:43:53,443 --> 01:43:58,646
with his dedication to this community over all these years, that he would wholeheartedly do that.

719
01:43:59,926 --> 01:44:06,930
So I honestly was shocked by the outcome of that meeting.

720
01:44:08,090 --> 01:44:10,772
It didn't even enter my mind as a possibility.

721
01:44:11,272 --> 01:44:21,177
Had I thought that that was a possibility, I would have, like I do usually, hey, important things are being discussed and put it on social media, please come.

722
01:44:22,120 --> 01:44:28,401
right, please come, or I would have requested that the meeting be televised, because I have done that also in the past.

723
01:44:29,061 --> 01:44:33,482
And I know we're getting new cameras in different areas, so we can do that.

724
01:44:34,902 --> 01:44:38,183
Because transparency is extremely important.

725
01:44:39,043 --> 01:44:49,405
And people not finding out important information online is, they feel insulted to find it out that way.

726
01:44:52,209 --> 01:45:06,023
I don't know what to say about the outcome of the meeting, but I can own that I did bring it forward and did not tell a push for it to be, because I thought it was just an interest, you know, an interim person stepping in for two months.

727
01:45:07,084 --> 01:45:07,444
Thank you.

728
01:45:07,544 --> 01:45:07,704
Ms.

729
01:45:07,744 --> 01:45:08,105
Mustone.

730
01:45:08,425 --> 01:45:11,488
Thank you, Maribel.

731
01:45:11,808 --> 01:45:16,693
I don't know about everyone, but likewise, I thought someone who was in administration was going to step in.

732
01:45:17,405 --> 01:45:19,766
not realizing that's not in their contract.

733
01:45:19,886 --> 01:45:32,232
So when we did receive multiple angry emails that night and the next morning, I did respond saying, I went in assuming, shame on me, that someone in administration would step into that role per contract.

734
01:45:32,692 --> 01:45:39,395
The other option was that the Massachusetts Association School Committees can take someone almost like an emergency superintendent.

735
01:45:39,956 --> 01:45:45,098
So to me, having a middle man or middle woman come in for eight weeks, try to transition,

736
01:45:45,935 --> 01:45:50,318
while we have, I almost feel like Dr. Maurice is like the Phoenix out of the ashes.

737
01:45:50,418 --> 01:45:54,040
Like this is going to be a whole new public school system.

738
01:45:54,840 --> 01:46:11,309
And I did not think that was the best choice to have a middle person, um, that I think Mr. Velson is, has the knowledge and the history to give our new superintendent and just looking forward that we needed that transition to be smoothly done.

739
01:46:11,329 --> 01:46:11,390
And,

740
01:46:12,884 --> 01:46:20,687
I know people don't agree with that, but I think it would have been more detrimental to our school system to bring someone in for eight weeks, and I stand by that decision.

741
01:46:21,527 --> 01:46:22,127
Mr. Seng.

742
01:46:22,147 --> 01:46:26,329
Do you have a microphone there?

743
01:46:26,569 --> 01:46:26,829
I don't.

744
01:46:26,889 --> 01:46:29,030
Okay, step up.

745
01:46:29,490 --> 01:46:29,950
There you go.

746
01:46:31,651 --> 01:46:41,034
Okay, well, I thank you for coming up and saying what a lot of our community is thinking and has been thinking throughout the past few years.

747
01:46:41,847 --> 01:46:50,233
And I'll say, when I read the notice for that meeting, I also didn't take it as you would take the vote that you took.

748
01:46:51,193 --> 01:46:54,876
And a lot of adults didn't take it that way either.

749
01:46:55,276 --> 01:46:59,259
And I think the notice did say exactly what the meeting would be about.

750
01:46:59,639 --> 01:47:00,220
It didn't lie.

751
01:47:00,280 --> 01:47:01,240
There were no lies in it.

752
01:47:01,721 --> 01:47:02,901
It stated the truth.

753
01:47:03,382 --> 01:47:07,004
But there's a part of it that includes communication.

754
01:47:09,133 --> 01:47:14,296
communicating to school committee members, to the general public about what the meeting might entail.

755
01:47:14,796 --> 01:47:20,440
And because of laws, you can't talk outside of a meeting.

756
01:47:20,460 --> 01:47:22,421
That's the problem.

757
01:47:22,861 --> 01:47:26,523
Yeah, and that's a huge problem that acts as a roadblock.

758
01:47:26,583 --> 01:47:37,069
But maybe allowing the public to know via social media, which you guys are all very good about, but to know via social media what

759
01:47:37,910 --> 01:47:41,471
might happen in a meeting, and to tell people, come.

760
01:47:41,631 --> 01:47:42,391
Come to this meeting.

761
01:47:42,811 --> 01:47:44,132
I think that really helps out.

762
01:47:44,972 --> 01:47:55,795
I'll say, from the student perspective, when we read that on Facebook, or when our friends texted the news, there were two reactions, generally.

763
01:47:56,075 --> 01:47:59,056
One was, what the heck?

764
01:47:59,536 --> 01:48:01,016
How did this just suddenly happen?

765
01:48:01,456 --> 01:48:05,297
And the other reaction was, oh, he was in for it.

766
01:48:05,477 --> 01:48:07,178
We knew that this would happen anyways.

767
01:48:07,987 --> 01:48:11,490
And, you know, both reactions aren't positive for our community.

768
01:48:11,591 --> 01:48:16,956
It's not positive for the school community, not positive for the general public, not positive for Mr. Bellson and his leadership.

769
01:48:17,857 --> 01:48:20,259
And I think a more open culture.

770
01:48:21,673 --> 01:48:30,318
the so-called new Medford, I think that's what we want to try and foster, what we want to try and sponsor, and how we deal with these issues going on.

771
01:48:30,818 --> 01:48:47,727
So being more open about what meetings might entail, and even, I would say, try more to advertise the committee of the whole meetings, because they're kind of put aside, and they allow for a more relaxed context, but I think it's important for people to know that these are important meetings,

772
01:48:49,272 --> 01:48:51,074
important stuff gets done in these meetings.

773
01:48:51,194 --> 01:48:52,455
I think that's super important.

774
01:48:53,396 --> 01:48:56,078
And I know Mr. Rousseau does this.

775
01:48:56,138 --> 01:48:57,259
He does town halls.

776
01:48:57,439 --> 01:48:59,861
He does meet the school committee member.

777
01:49:00,281 --> 01:49:04,344
And I think that's a great way for people in the community to engage with school committee members.

778
01:49:04,565 --> 01:49:09,008
So I say we have to take a step back, look at the bigger issue.

779
01:49:09,028 --> 01:49:09,729
It's about trust.

780
01:49:10,690 --> 01:49:14,533
And we need to build that trust between the general public and the Medford School Committee.

781
01:49:14,573 --> 01:49:17,115
And there's trust, but it can be stronger.

782
01:49:18,331 --> 01:49:19,091
Thank you, Justin.

783
01:49:19,912 --> 01:49:21,052
Very eloquent, Justin.

784
01:49:21,072 --> 01:49:24,794
Thank you.

785
01:49:24,834 --> 01:49:24,994
Ms.

786
01:49:25,034 --> 01:49:26,635
Kretz.

787
01:49:26,815 --> 01:49:47,504
Yes, so I, too, that night, I knew we were having a meeting, and we hadn't been able to talk about who would be the interim superintendent, so we got to talk that night, and I thought maybe somebody would be stepping up into that place, but we did have to make a decision in the best interest of everybody, like the students and the staffing,

788
01:49:48,122 --> 01:49:50,823
while we waited to hire our new superintendent.

789
01:49:50,883 --> 01:50:03,607
So, you know, I stand by my decision, and it was more of in the best interest of the schools and the students to keeping, you know, so we would have the training until the end of the school year.

790
01:50:03,627 --> 01:50:07,528
Because I have been getting a lot of questions from parents, who's gonna be the superintendent?

791
01:50:07,968 --> 01:50:09,269
And there's also been confusion.

792
01:50:09,689 --> 01:50:11,849
Some people thought we already hired a superintendent.

793
01:50:12,110 --> 01:50:14,310
So it's just been a little bit of confusion all around.

794
01:50:15,631 --> 01:50:16,411
But so,

795
01:50:17,105 --> 01:50:20,266
I stand by the decision that I made that night, as well.

796
01:50:20,586 --> 01:50:21,086
Thank you, Ms.

797
01:50:21,106 --> 01:50:21,366
Kratz.

798
01:50:21,586 --> 01:50:22,307
Mr. Benedetto?

799
01:50:22,427 --> 01:50:23,647
Thank you so much, Mayburg.

800
01:50:24,107 --> 01:50:32,049
I still have some questions, so I need some transparency and clarity on what exactly the superintendent's role is for the rest of this year.

801
01:50:32,450 --> 01:50:37,611
Will he have whole power as the superintendent?

802
01:50:37,651 --> 01:50:43,733
Will he be hiring and moving people and promoting people and providing raises?

803
01:50:44,200 --> 01:50:49,702
And I also heard a few rumors that he's telling people that he's going to be here beyond June 30th.

804
01:50:50,443 --> 01:50:51,823
Is that a possibility?

805
01:50:51,923 --> 01:50:54,064
Is there something about that happening?

806
01:50:54,644 --> 01:50:59,987
I just want to put it all out here while we're on camera and everybody's in the room.

807
01:51:00,607 --> 01:51:05,449
I just have these general questions and if someone could answer them for me and any other questions that come up.

808
01:51:06,149 --> 01:51:12,752
I just want to know are the rules we put in place in February for him to continue to April 30th still in place?

809
01:51:13,387 --> 01:51:16,049
or have they been removed?

810
01:51:16,149 --> 01:51:18,411
I'm really not sure what we voted for that night.

811
01:51:18,851 --> 01:51:21,553
None of those other restrictions have been removed.

812
01:51:22,254 --> 01:51:33,462
So he cannot hire people or move people or give raises or promotions unless it's like something to just provide services till June 30th.

813
01:51:33,603 --> 01:51:40,628
Anything beyond that, our new superintendent would be making those choices like department heads and all of that.

814
01:51:41,268 --> 01:51:42,069
Yes, of course.

815
01:51:42,550 --> 01:51:54,641
And the rumors that I'm hearing that he's telling people that he might be staying past June 30th, has anybody talked to him about doing any consulting beyond that point?

816
01:51:55,842 --> 01:51:58,104
No, this body has not talked about that.

817
01:51:58,864 --> 01:51:59,024
Ms.

818
01:51:59,044 --> 01:52:00,586
Van de Kloot.

819
01:52:00,606 --> 01:52:08,733
Mayor Burke, I just think that there may be positions that we want the superintendent to move on, and so I'm not,

820
01:52:09,442 --> 01:52:10,762
excluding that as a potential.

821
01:52:10,822 --> 01:52:12,143
But they have to be reviewed by us.

822
01:52:12,243 --> 01:52:15,203
Yes, but they would be, we would be part of that discussion.

823
01:52:15,463 --> 01:52:24,565
Now, of course, you know, um, and you know, I think the superintendent has made it very clear that he would also want to include, uh, the superintendent elect as well.

