there was only one thing that was important, and that is, what is in the best interest of the Medford Public Schools right now to ensure an effective transition to the next superintendent?

1033
02:10:19,230 --> 02:10:31,957
So, if it, in the, as we now make that transition to a new superintendent, I have no problem at all revisiting that policy, taking a look at it, but essentially, it's going to stand.

1034
02:10:32,537 --> 02:10:33,918
But, you know,

1035
02:10:35,548 --> 02:10:46,650
For me, the big question of who do we hear, school committee members heard from a lot of people, a lot of people.

1036
02:10:47,350 --> 02:10:58,792
And of course, there's been a very vocal segment of the community who's been very out there, who's been very upset with Mr. Belson, and there's been a whole lot of other people who've supported him.

1037
02:11:00,172 --> 02:11:02,793
I feel that we are elected

1038
02:11:04,300 --> 02:11:19,568
in the most difficult circumstances to keep our eye on the prize and be able to separate ourselves from all the different opinions we hear, no matter how difficult it is, and say, what is the most important thing going forward?

1039
02:11:21,189 --> 02:11:25,291
For me, it was to say, how do we make the best transition?

1040
02:11:25,451 --> 02:11:26,392
And in my mind,

1041
02:11:27,135 --> 02:11:39,000
It was at this point, given the circumstances that presented itself, it was to keep a experienced superintendent who had dedicated his life to Medford to move forward through the next eight weeks.

1042
02:11:41,121 --> 02:11:48,424
And I understand where your reasoning comes from, but with all due respect, you've known for months that the deputy was retiring.

1043
02:11:48,444 --> 02:11:56,227
