02:20:47,170 --> 02:20:50,991
We have a paper.

1139
02:20:51,071 --> 02:20:53,951
Traditionally, we have rejected school choice in this community.

1140
02:20:54,231 --> 02:20:56,932
Is there a motion on the floor to reject school choice?

1141
02:20:57,392 --> 02:21:00,473
Mr. Russo, seconded by Ms.

1142
02:21:00,493 --> 02:21:01,073
Vander Kloof.

1143
02:21:01,453 --> 02:21:02,413
Roll call vote, please.

1144
02:21:09,492 --> 02:21:16,677
quick summary is that under school choice people can

1145
02:21:17,430 --> 02:21:21,671
come to our school district for a very low amount of money if we have open seats.

1146
02:21:22,531 --> 02:21:32,494
And the cost that we would receive or the compensation received is not worth it to us, and we would have to educate people that would take seats from other people.

1147
02:21:32,894 --> 02:21:35,034
It just doesn't work under the current rule.

1148
02:21:35,355 --> 02:21:40,836
If you're a school system that has such open seats and you have no revenue coming in, maybe it makes sense.

1149
02:21:40,876 --> 02:21:41,856
That's not our situation.

1150
02:21:43,037 --> 02:21:44,777
We have to notify the state by a certain date.

1151
02:21:45,645 --> 02:21:46,605
Roll call vote, Ms.

1152
02:21:46,645 --> 02:21:48,446
Kretz, to reject school choice.

1153
02:21:50,327 --> 02:21:50,607
Yes.

1154
02:21:50,627 --> 02:21:53,969
I was just waiting for the wording.

1155
02:21:59,051 --> 02:22:01,812
Yes, seven in the affirmative, zero in the negative, motion passes.

1156
02:22:03,893 --> 02:22:08,395
Report on middle school, school year 18-19 enrollment and selection.

1157
02:22:11,477 --> 02:22:11,617
Ms.

1158
02:22:11,637 --> 02:22:11,997
Nelson.

1159
02:22:13,678 --> 02:22:14,118
Good evening.

1160
02:22:15,547 --> 02:22:21,789
From the report, you can see a little bit of the history of what we've been doing over the past several years.

1161
02:22:22,789 --> 02:22:37,053
Since the new middle schools opened in 2001, parents of students in grade 5 have been allowed to choose the middle school that they would like their child to attend, starting in 6th grade.

1162
02:22:37,553 --> 02:22:42,134
This system worked very well for a number of years, back and forth a little bit, sometimes the McGlynn

1163
02:22:42,696 --> 02:22:51,959
had more kids, sometimes the Andrews went back and forth, until this year, when we really had a big difference in enrollment.

1164
02:22:52,559 --> 02:22:59,842
And as you know, this past school year, we had several more fifth graders opting to go to the Andrews.

1165
02:23:00,482 --> 02:23:06,444
In total, that was 43, which is more than one class, almost two classes of youngsters.

1166
02:23:07,404 --> 02:23:08,865
So as we began to

1167
02:23:10,692 --> 02:23:16,856
think about moving forward and how we were going to handle the choice situation.

1168
02:23:17,737 --> 02:23:22,200
With your approval, we put the following items in place for this year.

1169
02:23:22,220 --> 02:23:23,261
We made some changes.

1170
02:23:23,941 --> 02:23:31,246
I will say, too, that the numbers of the Andrews of the students in grade six going to grade seven appears to be constant.

1171
02:23:31,266 --> 02:23:35,629
So they're still going to have that larger group in moving into grade seven.

1172
02:23:35,649 --> 02:23:38,351
There doesn't seem to be any movement out at this point.

1173
02:23:39,805 --> 02:23:49,369
Again, this year we decided to do things differently because there had been some things that we felt could be improved upon, one of which was the returning of the choice forms.

1174
02:23:50,430 --> 02:23:53,171
Up until this year, parents had options.

1175
02:23:53,291 --> 02:24:00,894
They could return them to the school, they could return them to the parent center in person, they could return them to the parent center by mail.

1176
02:24:02,135 --> 02:24:08,037
And this led to some confusion because there were deadlines and people felt that they truly had sent it in by the deadline,

1177
02:24:08,505 --> 02:24:09,325
but it didn't arrive.

1178
02:24:09,385 --> 02:24:15,548
So there were all kinds, whenever you have choice of how you do something, there always leaves room for issues.

1179
02:24:15,948 --> 02:24:18,869
So we decided to have a process that was uniform.

1180
02:24:19,189 --> 02:24:25,492
And we said this year, all forms would be returned to the school where the child was going to school.

1181
02:24:25,872 --> 02:24:29,894
And that's worked very well because we could track all the forms as they came in.

1182
02:24:30,514 --> 02:24:35,936
We also wanted parents to have verification that they had actually turned their form in.

1183
02:24:36,406 --> 02:24:42,851
So every school, in their own way, gave the parent a number or a form that said that the form was passed.

1184
02:24:42,871 --> 02:24:47,435
And so nobody could say, gee, I sent it in, but it must have gone somewhere else.

1185
02:24:47,835 --> 02:24:52,098
So again, we felt that process, by tightening up that, that was very helpful.

1186
02:24:53,119 --> 02:25:01,686
The second thing that we made changes on is that we decided that the open houses, we'd make them more consistent in the presentation.

1187
02:25:02,226 --> 02:25:03,948
And Dr. Riccadeli and I, as you know,

1188
02:25:04,874 --> 02:25:12,499
And we basically facilitated the presentation for the McGlynn, which was first, and the Andrews, which was second.

1189
02:25:13,200 --> 02:25:18,523
And again, we had the principals there, because we don't want them to be hidden, and we had the tours of the buildings.

1190
02:25:19,063 --> 02:25:33,573
But we gave a presentation to really emphasize to parents that the education opportunities at both schools were equal, and that students were going to get an education, the same education, curriculum-wise, in either school.

1191
02:25:34,273 --> 02:25:43,037
So we felt that was an improvement, and we asked parents to return forms to the schools, their child's elementary school, by April 2nd.

1192
02:25:43,898 --> 02:25:44,278
All right?

1193
02:25:45,378 --> 02:25:50,581
And then again, we also put in place that there would be choice.

1194
02:25:50,601 --> 02:25:53,182
There was almost like two steps to the process.

1195
02:25:53,202 --> 02:26:03,187
There would be choice, but if the choice resulted in imbalance, a large imbalance, the committee voted that they would have a partial lottery, so to even out the numbers.

1196
02:26:03,990 --> 02:26:15,976
And again, we were hoping that the choice, the numbers would be even, but as you can see from the data that I gave you at the second sheet, they're not.

1197
02:26:16,016 --> 02:26:28,123
In fact, in reviewing some of the items with special education today with Joan Bowen, we actually have two more students that need to be placed at the Andrews.

1198
02:26:28,223 --> 02:26:30,284
So it brings it to a total of

1199
02:26:30,940 --> 02:26:32,782
Entering sixth grade is at the Andrews, 176.

1200
02:26:33,202 --> 02:26:36,645
Entering students at the McGlynn is 118.

1201
02:26:38,006 --> 02:26:40,228
So we're looking to the committee for next steps.

1202
02:26:41,208 --> 02:26:46,012
Parents are waiting to hear definitely what school the children will be attending.

1203
02:26:46,553 --> 02:26:49,575
And obviously, principals are eager to start scheduling.

1204
02:26:49,615 --> 02:26:53,418
And you really can't start the scheduling process until you have numbers.

1205
02:26:54,019 --> 02:26:59,263
So again, moving forward, we, again, need some guidance on

1206
02:26:59,790 --> 02:27:01,270
how to conduct this partial lottery.

1207
02:27:01,310 --> 02:27:13,473
You can see the different schools where the imbalance is the greatest, and we have to go from there, and I think we probably need to give it some thought, but not too long, because people are eager to move forward.

1208
02:27:16,573 --> 02:27:17,533
Mr. Rousseau, sorry.

1209
02:27:19,474 --> 02:27:20,094
Thank you, Ms.

1210
02:27:20,114 --> 02:27:22,294
Nelson.

1211
02:27:22,794 --> 02:27:25,295
Some parents did not submit a form back.

1212
02:27:26,375 --> 02:27:26,835
Very few.

1213
02:27:27,785 --> 02:27:36,031
Were there efforts to contact those families to find out what their preferences were?

1214
02:27:37,132 --> 02:27:43,077
There were very few that didn't return them, and I'm not quite sure what individual principals did.

1215
02:27:43,157 --> 02:27:46,139
I can find out, again, at their age, from school to school.

1216
02:27:46,720 --> 02:27:54,185
But again, what we did is we found that, again, as you can see, that there were some that had no requests.

1217
02:27:56,574 --> 02:28:03,096
basically the programs like the EL students did not have choice because they do have to go to the McGlynn, so there were things like that.

1218
02:28:03,496 --> 02:28:12,839
And again, with Joan Bowen today, we were able to make sure we had the students who needed to be placed in certain special education programs in the appropriate building.

1219
02:28:16,395 --> 02:28:19,257
spent entirely too many hours on these numbers this weekend.

1220
02:28:20,738 --> 02:28:23,721
Thank you for getting this to us as early as possible.

1221
02:28:24,662 --> 02:28:34,109
You know, reviewing this was not really very fun, because the imbalance was so pronounced.

1222
02:28:34,769 --> 02:28:45,097
And I just, you know, when I was trying to figure out how we would handle this, other than the fact that we would have to have a partial lottery, you know, I was trying to figure out, like, what are the principles that I feel are important,

1223
02:28:46,363 --> 02:28:53,365
The basic principle that I felt was the only one that I could stand on was that each school sends half their kids to each middle school.

1224
02:28:54,305 --> 02:29:13,929
And because the selection between the schools from the individual elementary schools is very pronounced in a couple of the schools, that means that a couple of the elementary schools will have a much greater amount of getting their non-preferred school.

1225
02:29:14,450 --> 02:29:15,790
And I just want to make sure that

1226
02:29:18,431 --> 02:29:24,617
So I've never had any doubt that this process is perfectly fair and there's no shenanigans going on.

1227
02:29:25,078 --> 02:29:39,973
But for this year in particular, I really think it's important that when the randomization is happening, that there is at least one school committee member present, that the public is free to show up if they want.

